5IH.F.summary: INTOSOL Holdings PLC engages in travel business worldwide. It also owns, manages, and leases hotels and villas, as well as a Leadwood safari lodge. The company operates Oceans Wilderness, a boutique hotel located in South Africa. It also provides private travel design solutions; and VIRTOSOL, a proprietary software that allows the customer to preview their holiday. The company was founded in 2002 and is headquartered in Garbsen, Germany. INTOSOL Holdings PLC is a subsidiary of RSP Beteiligungs GmbH.

A8N.MU.summary: aovo Touristik AG provides tour and travel services primarily in Germany and rest of Europe. The company markets its services through direct sales and online. aovo Touristik AG was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Hanover, Germany.

HOC.DE.summary: HolidayCheck Group AG engages in the transaction-based online business in the fields of travel and weather in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, Austria, Belgium, Poland, Germany, and Switzerland. It operates a range of hotel rating and holiday booking portals, which offer package tours, cruise, hotels, and rental car booking services; and WeerOnline.nl, an advertising based weather portal. The company also operates as a tour operator. The company was formerly known as TOMORROW FOCUS AG and changed its name to HolidayCheck Group AG in June 2016. HolidayCheck Group AG is headquartered in Munich, Germany.

TUI.L.short_name: TUI AG ORD REG SHS NPV (DI)
TUI.L.summary: TUI AG, together with its subsidiaries, provides tourism services worldwide. It operates hotels and resorts under the Robinson, Riu, TUI Blue, Blue Diamond, and TUI Magic Life brands. The company is also involved in the tour operation and airlines businesses. In addition, it operates cruise liners. The company operates a fleet of 1,600 travel agencies and online portals; 5 airlines with approximately 150 aircrafts; and 17 cruise liners, as well as approximately 400 hotels. The company was formerly known as Preussag AG and changed its name to TUI AG in June 2002. TUI AG is headquartered in Hanover, Germany.
